<subSubSection pageId="96" pageNumber="696" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="96.[163,1369,296,562]" pageId="96" pageNumber="696">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[165,518,371,405]" pageId="96" pageNumber="696">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Endangered on The IUCN Red List. Bannister’s Mosaic-tailed Rat is known only from type locality and from four individuals collected within a range ofless than 570 km?, which is threatened by logging. The species seems able to adapt, at least to some extent, to anthropogenic perturbations.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
